    <briefdescription>
<para>Interface for receiving interactive events from <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1InteractiveTrait" kindref="compound">InteractiveTrait</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>When <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1InteractiveTrait" kindref="compound">InteractiveTrait</ref> is attached to a <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1View" kindref="compound">View</ref> whose <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1ViewImpl" kindref="compound">ViewImpl</ref> implements this interface, the trait calls these methods directly before emitting the corresponding signals. This avoids the overhead of adding signal connections for subclass event handling.</para>
<para>Typically implemented by <ref refid="classDali_1_1Ui_1_1Integration_1_1InteractiveViewImpl" kindref="compound">InteractiveViewImpl</ref> and its subclasses. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
